<section id="TMBInteractions"class="section-padding-large">
    {% comment %} <div class="bg rellax" data-rellax-percentage="0.5" data-rellax-speed="-10">
        <img src="{{'/assets/images/tmb/bg.jpg' | url}}" ></img>
    </div> {% endcomment %}
    <div class="container text-light relative">
        <h3 class="mb-8">Interaction Highlights</h3>
        <p class="h6 mb-16">Great care was placed in creating eye catching and performant interactions and animations. I worked alongside the design team to bring their ideas to life in a scope and performance friendly way.</p>
        <div class="tmb-interaction-wrapper">
            <div class="tmb-interaction-item-full">
                <div class="video">
                    <video muted autoplay loop class="image-cover">
                        <source src="{{ '/assets/video/tmb/reach.webm' | url }}" type="video/webm">
                    </video>
                </div>
                <div class="info-bottom">
                    <p class="tag">Pure CSS | 3D CSS and CSS variables</p>
                    <p class="copy">Nested CSS 3D transforms were used to create a responsive 3D grid. A dotted stroke is applied to an svg arch, and is animated using CSS keyframes. CSS variables are used to easily change the gradient to reflect the brand colors via a varible in the CMS. Elements like the arch and impact point can be changed based on screensize using a CSS media query. Additionally, the CSS varibles used here are used throughout the page, things such as button colors and accent colors can be effected on a per-page basis by modifying a single set of variables.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="tmb-interaction-item-half">
                <div class="video">
                    <video muted autoplay loop class="image-cover">
                        <source src="{{ '/assets/video/tmb/data.webm' | url }}" type="video/webm">
                    </video>
                </div>
                <div class="info-bottom">
                        <p class="tag">CSS + Light JS | CSS Keyframes With Some JS Help </p>
                        <p class="copy">The graphic is a flexbox of spans. Each span is given a random CSS timing variable that controls the speed the span pulses. Every 2000ms 30 nodes are chosen at random and their colors are changed to a random color from a list. CSS was chosen over canvas for iteration speed, compatability, and scaling.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="tmb-interaction-item-half">
                <div class="video">
                    <video muted autoplay loop class="image-cover">
                        <source src="{{ '/assets/video/tmb/cloud.webm' | url }}" type="video/webm">
                    </video>
                </div>
                <div class="info-bottom">
                        <p class="tag">Pure CSS | Fake Parallax With Offset Transition Timing</p>
                        <p class="copy">Multiple layers of full sized, absolutly positioned divs overlay eachother. Each div contains a few positioned circles of video or colors. Each layer is given a sligtly different transition timing and starting scale. On hover, the layer scales are set to 1, and the different timings create a simple and performant parallaxing effect. Each circle can be repositioned to account for screen sizes.</p>
                </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
